===Alternative forms===
* Bactriana, Bākhtar in [[Persian]], also Bhalika in Indian languages, and [[Ta-Hia]] in Chinese.

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|Βακτριανή|lang=grc}}. See also {{etyl|peo|-}} {{term|𐎲𐎠𐎧𐎫𐎼𐎡𐏁|tr=Bâxtriš|lang=peo}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈbæktɹɪə/|lang=en}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# The ancient [[Greek]] name of the country between the range of the [[Hindu Kush]] and the [[Amu Darya]] in the [[Middle East]], encompassing parts of northern [[Afghanistan]], eastern [[Turkmenistan]], southern [[Uzbekistan]], [[Tajikistan]] and northern [[Pakistan]].

